The paper deals with generative visual dialog models, which involve both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses reinforcement learning and the use of auxiliary objectives, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach using automatic metrics and human studies, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
